6. The dialogue-metres of the Latin Dramatists do not compare (as metres) very unfavourably with their Greek originals in the few cases in which the latter have been preserved. Take for example the opening lines of Ennius' &ledea Ewul and Euripides' Medea:

Utinam ne in nemore Pelio securibus

caesa accidisset abiegna ad terram trabes,

neue inde nauis incohandi exordium

coepisset, quae nunc nominatur nomine

Argo, quia Argiui in ea delecti uiri

uecti petebant pellem inauratam arietis

Colchis, imperio regis Peliae, per dolum.

nam numquam era errans mea domo ecferret pedem Medea, animo aegra, amore saeuo saucia.
